[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'jginsburgn', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2019-01-01 04:55:22+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "I was trying to find out how to use a [`PopupMenu`][1] with RN. While browsing the documentation, I found no mention of how this would be possible without an external plugin. I jumped to searching in Google and found a small snippet, in a comment of [#3004][2] of react-native's git, referring to `UIManager` and its `showPopupMenu` API. I believe this is a powerful native feature of which documentation shall be not only in the [source code][3], but also in the docs website.

[1]: https://developer.android.com/reference/android/widget/PopupMenu
[2]: https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/3004#issuecomment-202598006
[3]: https://github.com/facebook/react-native/blob/39b68903463062f69c9120fab7e79fa2735b0b07/ReactAndroid/src/main/java/com/facebook/react/uimanager/NativeViewHierarchyManager.java#LC777", 'title': 'Missing documentation for UIManager', 'type': 'issue'}
